"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkdiogenes_docs=globalThis.webpackChunkdiogenes_docs||[]).push([[245],{1417(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"devlog-1-0-17","metadata":{"permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/devlog-1-0-17","editUrl":"https://github.com/efelleto/Diogenes/blog/2026-03-11-devlogs/2026-03-11-devlog-2.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-11-devlogs/2026-03-11-devlog-2.md","title":"DevLog #2 - Java 8 Support, Bug Fixes & Community","description":"After a focused sprint of fixes, refactoring, and documentation work, Diogenes 1.0.17 is live. This update is one of the most important since the project launched, not because of new features, but because of how much more stable, compatible, and accessible the ecosystem became.","date":"2026-03-11T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Announcement","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/announcement","description":"General news and important ecosystem updates."},{"inline":false,"label":"Release","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/release","description":"Official version launches and stable builds."},{"inline":false,"label":"SDK","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/sdk","description":"New features, bugfixes, and improvements for the Client SDK."},{"inline":false,"label":"Docs","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/docs","description":"Documentation updates, fixes, and new guides."}],"readingTime":3.58,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Eduardo Felleto","title":"Head Developer","url":"https://github.com/efelleto","page":{"permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/authors/efelleto"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/efelleto"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/142946087?s=400&u=19d31e0d5b6ea18304ababf40ddc3617db4c8de5&v=4","key":"efelleto"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"devlog-1-0-17","title":"DevLog #2 - Java 8 Support, Bug Fixes & Community","authors":["efelleto"],"tags":["announcement","release","sdk","docs"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"DevLog #3 - Server config simplification & SDK Fix","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/devlog-3"}},"content":"After a focused sprint of fixes, refactoring, and documentation work, **Diogenes 1.0.17** is live. This update is one of the most important since the project launched, not because of new features, but because of how much more **stable, compatible, and accessible** the ecosystem became.\\n\\nHere\'s everything that changed.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \u2615 Java 8 Support\\n\\nThe biggest change in this release: **the SDK now supports Java 8 and above.**\\n\\nPreviously, the SDK required Java 21, which excluded a significant portion of the Minecraft server ecosystem, especially older 1.8.x servers that still run on legacy JDKs.\\n\\nStarting from `1.0.17`, the SDK is fully compatible with:\\n\\n| Java Version | Supported |\\n| :--- | :--- |\\n| Java 8 | \u2705 |\\n| Java 11 | \u2705 |\\n| Java 17 | \u2705 |\\n| Java 21 | \u2705 |\\n\\nThis change required a complete rework of how the fat JAR is assembled. More on that below:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1b Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release resolves **three critical issues** that were introduced during the Java 8 migration. They appeared sequentially \u2014 each fix revealed the next \u2014 but all share the same root cause: how Kotlin libraries were being bundled and relocated inside the SDK JAR.\\n\\n<details>\\n<summary><strong>Fix #1 \u2014 `ExceptionInInitializerError` on authentication (1.0.15 \u2192 1.0.16)</strong></summary>\\n\\n**What happened:**\\nThe `kotlin-reflect` library was being relocated inside the fat JAR (e.g. `kotlin.*` \u2192 `dev.efelleto.diogenes.libs.kotlin.*`). This broke an internal mechanism in `kotlin-reflect` that loads built-in type metadata from `.kotlin_builtins` resource files using hardcoded classpath paths.\\n\\n**Error:**\\n```\\nCaused by: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Resource not found in classpath:\\ndev/efelleto/diogenes/libs/kotlin/...kotlin_builtins\\n```\\n\\n**Fix:**\\n`kotlin-reflect` is now fully excluded from the fat JAR. Since it modifies internal JVM behavior and relies on hardcoded resource paths, it cannot be safely relocated.\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n<details>\\n<summary><strong>Fix #2 \u2014 `ClassNotFoundException: kotlinx.coroutines.CoroutineScope` (1.0.16 \u2192 1.0.17)</strong></summary>\\n\\n**What happened:**\\nAfter excluding `kotlin-reflect`, `kotlinx-coroutines` was also missing from the JAR. The Ktor CIO engine depends heavily on coroutines, and since the target servers (1.8.8 vanilla) don\'t provide Kotlin at runtime, the class was simply not found.\\n\\n**Error:**\\n```\\njava.lang.ClassNotFoundException: kotlinx.coroutines.CoroutineScope\\n```\\n\\n**Fix:**\\n`kotlinx-coroutines-core` is now bundled inside the fat JAR without relocation, ensuring it\'s always available regardless of the server environment.\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n<details>\\n<summary><strong>Fix #3 \u2014 Banner log pollution on server startup (1.0.17)</strong></summary>\\n\\n**What happened:**\\nThe Diogenes ASCII banner was being printed inside a `runTaskLater` (10 tick delay), which caused Spigot\'s own startup messages to interleave with the banner output in the console.\\n\\n**Before:**\\n```\\n__________________________________________________________________________________\\n    _____^_\\n   ...\\n__________________________________________________________________________________\\n[INFO]: The server will be available in 4 seconds.   \u2190 intruder\\n[INFO]: The server will be available in 3 seconds.   \u2190 intruder\\n[INFO]: AUTH: Successfully authenticated.\\n```\\n\\n**After:**\\n```\\n__________________________________________________________________________________\\n    _____^_\\n   ...\\n__________________________________________________________________________________\\n\\n[INFO]: The server will be available in 4 seconds.\\n[INFO]: The server will be available in 3 seconds.\\n[INFO]: AUTH: Successfully authenticated.\\n```\\n\\n**Fix:**\\nThe banner is now printed synchronously during `onEnable()`, before any async task is scheduled.\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 SDK Build Rework\\n\\nThe entire fat JAR assembly strategy was redesigned. Here\'s the final configuration that makes everything work cleanly:\\n\\n| Library | Strategy | Reason |\\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\\n| `kotlin-stdlib` | Bundled, not relocated | Server doesn\'t provide it |\\n| `kotlin-reflect` | Excluded | Breaks with any relocation |\\n| `kotlinx-coroutines` | Bundled, not relocated | Required by Ktor CIO |\\n| `kotlinx.atomicfu` | Bundled + relocated | Transitive dep, may conflict |\\n| `io.ktor` | Bundled + relocated | Avoid classpath conflicts |\\n| `com.google.gson` | Bundled + relocated | Avoid classpath conflicts |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcda Documentation Overhaul\\n\\nAll documentation pages were reviewed and updated to reflect the current state of the project:\\n\\n- **Getting Started:** Java requirement corrected to **Java 8+**, Gradle snippet fixed to proper Kotlin DSL syntax.\\n- **Integration:** Fully rewritten with a parameter reference table, step-by-step authentication flow, and a complete error handling table.\\n- **Installation:** Fixed inconsistency between `config.yml` and `settings.yml` references. Configuration block is now a proper YAML example.\\n- **Discord Commands:** Fixed header hierarchy and standardized formatting.\\n- **Security Flow:** Minor formatting cleanup.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcac Community\\n\\nThe **Diogenes Discord server** is being set up. It will be the central hub for:\\n\\n- Getting help with installation and integration\\n- Reporting bugs and suggesting features\\n- Following development updates in real time\\n- Connecting with other developers using the ecosystem\\n\\nAn invite link will be shared here and in the README as soon as the server is ready. Stay tuned.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\uddfa\ufe0f What\'s Next\\n\\n- **Sinope Layer:** JAR obfuscation CLI tool. The groundwork is laid, active development starts next.\\n- **Discord invite:** Community server going live soon.\\n---\\n\\nThanks for following the project. If Diogenes has been useful to you, consider leaving a \u2b50 on [GitHub](https://github.com/efelleto/Diogenes), it helps a lot.\\n\\n*\u2014 Eduardo Felleto*"},{"id":"devlog-3","metadata":{"permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/devlog-3","editUrl":"https://github.com/efelleto/Diogenes/blog/2026-03-11-devlogs/2026-03-11-devlog-3.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-11-devlogs/2026-03-11-devlog-3.md","title":"DevLog #3 - Server config simplification & SDK Fix","description":"Two small but meaningful releases back to back. 1.0.18 simplifies the server configuration system, and 1.0.19 fixes a critical SDK bug affecting servers running multiple licensed plugins simultaneously.","date":"2026-03-11T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Release","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/release","description":"Official version launches and stable builds."},{"inline":false,"label":"Backend","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/backend","description":"Updates on the Diogenes Server, MongoDB, and JDA Bot."},{"inline":false,"label":"SDK","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/sdk","description":"New features, bugfixes, and improvements for the Client SDK."}],"readingTime":2.47,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Eduardo Felleto","title":"Head Developer","url":"https://github.com/efelleto","page":{"permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/authors/efelleto"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/efelleto"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/142946087?s=400&u=19d31e0d5b6ea18304ababf40ddc3617db4c8de5&v=4","key":"efelleto"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"devlog-3","title":"DevLog #3 - Server config simplification & SDK Fix","authors":["efelleto"],"tags":["release","backend","sdk"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"DevLog #2 - Java 8 Support, Bug Fixes & Community","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/devlog-1-0-17"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome to the Diogenes DevLog","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/welcome-to-diogenes"}},"content":"Two small but meaningful releases back to back. **1.0.18** simplifies the server configuration system, and **1.0.19** fixes a critical SDK bug affecting servers running multiple licensed plugins simultaneously.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1.0.18 - Server Config Simplification\\n\\n### \ud83d\uddc2\ufe0f The Old Structure\\n\\nPreviously, the server generated a nested folder structure on first run:\\n\\n```\\ndiogenes-config/\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 server/\\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 config.yml\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 discord/\\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 messages.yml\\n```\\n\\nThis made sense in theory, but in practice it was unnecessary overhead. The `messages.yml` file contained Discord embed messages that are better handled at the Sinope layer, and the extra folders added friction for anyone setting up the server quickly.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u2705 The New Structure\\n\\nStarting from `1.0.18`, the server generates a single file at the root, right next to the JAR:\\n\\n```\\nDiogenesServer.jar\\nconfig.yml          \u2190 generated here on first run\\n```\\n\\nThe config file itself was also cleaned up. Two unused fields (`admin-role-id` and `log-channel-id`) were removed:\\n\\n```yaml\\nserver:\\n  port: 8080\\n  mongo-uri: \\"mongodb://localhost:27017\\"\\n\\ndiscord:\\n  bot-token: \\"YOUR_BOT_TOKEN_HERE\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f First Boot Messages\\n\\nThe first-run console output now follows the same visual standard as the rest of the server logs:\\n\\n**Before:**\\n```\\n[!] Config folder created on: /home/user/diogenes-config\\n[!] Please fill the information in ./diogenes-config/server/config.yml and restart.\\n```\\n\\n**After:**\\n```\\n[ INFO ] CONFIG: File created at: /home/user/config.yml\\n[ INFO ] CONFIG: Please fill config.yml and restart the server.\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u26a0\ufe0f Migration Note\\n\\nIf you are upgrading from a previous version, your old `diogenes-config/server/config.yml` will **not** be read automatically. Before restarting with `1.0.18`:\\n\\n1. Copy your `mongo-uri` and `bot-token` values from the old file.\\n2. Delete the `diogenes-config/` folder.\\n3. Run the new JAR \u2014 it will generate a fresh `config.yml` at the root.\\n4. Paste your credentials and restart.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1.0.19 \u2014 SDK Singleton Fix\\n\\n### \ud83d\udc1b The Problem\\n\\nWhen two or more plugins using the Diogenes SDK were loaded on the same server, they shared the same SDK instance \u2014 because `DiogenesSDK` was implemented as a Kotlin `object` (singleton).\\n\\nThis caused the second plugin to overwrite the `pluginFolder` of the first, making both plugins read from the same `license.yml` file. In practice, this meant the second plugin could authenticate using the first plugin\'s key without having its own license configured.\\n\\n```\\n[ INFO ] AUTH: Successfully authenticated. PRODUCT: plugin1     \u2190 correct\\n[ INFO ] AUTH: Successfully authenticated. PRODUCT: plugin2     \u2190 wrong, used plugin1\'s key\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u2705 The Fix\\n\\n`DiogenesSDK` was refactored from an `object` to a `class`. Each `init()` call now creates an isolated instance with its own `productId`, `baseUrl`, and `pluginFolder`.\\n\\n```\\nplugins/Plugin1/license.yml     \u2190 read by plugin1\'s instance\\nplugins/Plugin2/license.yml     \u2190 read by plugin2\'s instance\\n```\\n\\nThe public API is **unchanged** \u2014 your `onEnable()` code stays exactly the same:\\n\\n```java\\nDiogenesSDK.init(this, \\"your-product-id\\", \\"http://your-server:8080\\", () -> { ... });\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfa8 Banner Improvement\\n\\nThe ASCII banner now prints together with the authentication result, instead of appearing separately at the top of the log:\\n\\n```\\n__________________________________________________________________________________\\n\\n    _____^_\\n   ...\\n   / \\\\_/   0  \\\\        Diogenes 1.0.19\\n\\n[ INFO ] AUTH: Successfully authenticated. PRODUCT: plugin\\n__________________________________________________________________________________\\n```\\n\\nIf multiple plugins are loaded, only the first one prints the banner. Subsequent plugins print only their result line \u2014 keeping the console clean.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*\u2014 Eduardo Felleto*"},{"id":"welcome-to-diogenes","metadata":{"permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/welcome-to-diogenes","editUrl":"https://github.com/efelleto/Diogenes/blog/2026-03-10-welcome/2026-03-10-welcome.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-10-welcome/2026-03-10-welcome.md","title":"Welcome to the Diogenes DevLog","description":"Welcome to the official Diogenes DevLog. This is where we will document the evolution of our licensing ecosystem.","date":"2026-03-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Announcement","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/announcement","description":"General news and important ecosystem updates."},{"inline":false,"label":"Release","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/tags/release","description":"Official version launches and stable builds."}],"readingTime":0.37,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Eduardo Felleto","title":"Head Developer","url":"https://github.com/efelleto","page":{"permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/authors/efelleto"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/efelleto"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/142946087?s=400&u=19d31e0d5b6ea18304ababf40ddc3617db4c8de5&v=4","key":"efelleto"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome-to-diogenes","title":"Welcome to the Diogenes DevLog","authors":["efelleto"],"tags":["announcement","release"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"DevLog #3 - Server config simplification & SDK Fix","permalink":"/Diogenes/blog/devlog-3"}},"content":"Welcome to the official **Diogenes DevLog**. This is where we will document the evolution of our licensing ecosystem.\\n\\nToday marks a major milestone as we\'ve finalized the documentation for the **Server** and **SDK** modules. Our goal is to provide a seamless and secure experience for developers who want to protect their intellectual property without the headache of complex integrations.\\n\\n### What\'s coming next?\\n- **Sinope Layer:** Advanced obfuscation for JAR files.\\n\\n\\nStay tuned for more updates!"}]}}')}}]);